Wrapper class provide a way to use primitive data types (int, boolean, etc..) as objects
The table below shows the primitive type and the equivalent wrapper class:

Primitive Data Type:        Wrapper Class:
byte                        Byte
short                       Short
int                         Integer
long                        Long
float                       Float
double                      Double
boolean                     Boolean
char                        Character

You need wrapper class when working with Collection objects,
such as ArrayList, HashMap/Set etc.,
where primitive types cannot be used (the list can only store objects).

Example:
ArrayList<int> myNumbers = new ArrayList<int>(); // Invalid
ArrayList<Integer> myNumbers = new ArrayList<Integer>(); // Valid

